resource.name: LungCancerScreeningRecommendation
resource.title: Lung Cancer Screening Recommendation
resource.description: Adults aged 50 to 80 years (inclusive both ways, i.e., >=50, <= 80) who have a 30 pack-year smoking history and currently smoke or have quit within the past 15 years. Screening should be discontinued once a person has not smoked for 15 years (identical to inclusion criterion above) or develops a health problem that substantially limits life expectancy or the ability or willingness to have curative lung surgery (currently NOT taken into account.)
resource.purpose: Annual screening for lung cancer with low-dose computed tomography (LDCT)
